# Code Standards

## File Hygiene (enforced by ESLint)

- Max 300 lines per file (skip blanks and comments). If a file is approaching this, split it.
- Max 50 lines per function. Extract helpers, hooks, or utilities.
- If a folder exceeds ~12 files, create sub-folders.

## Package Manager

Use **bun** exclusively. Never npm, npx, or yarn.
`bun install`, `bun add`, `bun run`, `bunx`.

## Code Organization

- All types in `src/lib/types.ts`
- All Zod schemas in `src/lib/schemas.ts`
- All LLM prompts in `src/lib/prompts.ts`
- Do not scatter contracts across route files
- One shared `rhetoricalCoreSchema` reused by all analysis responses

## Architecture

- Schema-validated JSON via Zod `generateObject()`. No freeform markdown in the pipeline.
- Stable `segmentId` on every transcript segment. Every flag, chart point, and verdict traces back to an ID.
- `page.tsx` is a thin composition shell. All orchestration lives in `useTruthSession` hook.
- One analysis endpoint, one verification pipeline. No duplicate paths.

## Next.js

This version has breaking changes. Read the relevant guide in `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before writing any code. Heed deprecation notices.
